Approvals in Jenkins are used to pause a pipeline and wait for manual confirmation before proceeding to the next stage. This is commonly used 
before deploying to production or other sensitive environments.

The pipeline automatically builds, tests, and deploys to DEV/QA.
Before deploying to PROD, Jenkins pauses and waits for an authorized person to approve.


Usecase:

Build
   ↓
Unit Test
   ↓
Deploy to DEV
   ↓
Deploy to QA
   ↓
❓ Approval Required
   ↓
Deploy to PROD

pipeline {
    agent any

    stages {

        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                echo "Building Application..."
            }
        }

        stage('Deploy to DEV') {
            steps {
                echo "Deploying to DEV..."
            }
        }

        stage('Approval') {
        steps {
        script {
            def approver = input(
                message: 'Deploy to Production?',
                ok: 'Deploy',
                submitter: 'vamsi',
                submitterParameter: 'APPROVED_BY'
            )

            echo "Approved by: ${approver}"
        }
    }
}

        stage('Deploy to PROD') {
            steps {
                echo "Deploying to Production..."
            }
        }
    }
}


If pipeline ran user has Overall → Administer, Jenkins administrators can approve any input step regardless of the submitter list. If he is not in the list since he can approve due to
admin access.


Creating users without admin access can test this process.
